# Role charters (Layer 1)

When it is unclear **whose job** a piece of convmem maintenance or auditing work
is, read the matching card in `docs/role-charters.md`. Each card names the core
responsibilities, the easy-to-overlook duties, what is already mechanized, and
the Layer 2 register rows (`docs/standing-checks-register.json`) that role owns.

## Whose job is this? Read the card when…

- **Retrieval / ML** — tuning retrieval quality, adding a ranking signal, or
  investigating a slow/stale-feeling answer (recency-boost, latency budget).
- **Data / Knowledge** — adding an adapter, deciding whether a fact is stale, or
  before any bulk neutralize/delete (adapter parity, neutralize provenance).
- **Platform / Backend** — touching deploy scripts, changing `global_context_paths`
  merge order, or adding a stopgap rule with an expiry (ksweep sunset, merge order).
- **QA / Eval** — adding a new eval, interpreting a regression, or changing the
  judge model (provenance + judge-independence wiring).
- **SRE / Reliability** — closing a P0, adding a canary, or revisiting alert
  thresholds (exposure windows, escalation thresholds).
- **Technical Writer / Docs** — renaming/renumbering, writing a canon slice, or
  closing a decision discussion (cross-doc consistency, deferred-decision closure,
  charter-register consistency).
- **Tech Lead / EM** — sequencing, tier gating, go/no-go. Not delegated to an
  agent; kept in the charter for reference only.

## Standing checks

The state-dependent half of these duties is tracked in
`docs/standing-checks-register.json` and surfaced by `convmem doctor`
(`standing_register` check). Charter `register_refs` and register ids are kept in
sync by the `charter-register-consistency` probe.

